From f36fca912e5a8b484b5c26e36395da957c60e2b2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 16:25:37 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Wire up remaining ProjectActionMenu items: real folders,
 analytics, activity
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Move to Folder: adds a folder column on projects, a picker dialog
  (existing labels or create new), and db.ts helpers to list/set it.
- Analytics: new dialog showing real per-project stats (views, saved
  versions, deployments, database status, documentation coverage,
  visibility) pulled live from Supabase instead of a "coming soon" toast.
- Activity: new dialog showing a real per-project timeline built from
  actual timestamped rows (created/updated, deployments, database
  provisioning, documentation generation/edits, saved versions) — replaces
  the old redirect to the workspace-wide audit log, which never had
  anything written to it.
- Regenerated src/integrations/supabase/types.ts for the new folder column.

Every one of the 18 ProjectActionMenu items now performs a genuinely
working action.
